title: 8-Bit Louie Feminine Fit Long Sleeve Tee
body_html:
PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

The first Louie design I made since his passing (RIP) so this one is very special to me. I was inspired by vintage video games and those striped lines old TVs used to get when they broke. We kept it black and white with a pop of colour just for his tongue to make the design really stand out.

Note: We made this one a feminine fit, better suited to bodies with bust, hips & curves.

Art by Grace.

PRODUCT DETAILS

Regular fit Boat neck Breton top

Mid weight, 160 GSM, 100% combed cotton

5mm stripe, neck ribbing, side seamed, shoulder to shoulder tape, double needle hems, preshrunk to minimise shrinkage

title: A Children's Novel Hoodie
body_html:
PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

LONELY KIDS CLUB x BLACK BOOKS

LKC presents the Black Books range! A new collection inspired by the classic series about a book shop run by someone who doesn't really want to sell books and/or talk to people. And Manny. It's honestly the closest thing to our old retail store which was never consistently open and about the same level of cleanliness. We put together our top moments that would translate well onto clothing and tried doing something particularly special for a particularly special series.

Not affiliated with or directing any proceeds to raging TERF Graham Linehan.

Art by Claire Harrison.

PRODUCT DETAILS

Mid weight, 290 GSM 80% cotton 20% polyester anti-pill fleece

Featuring pullover hood, raglan sleeves, kangaroo pocket, lined hood, tonal drawcord
Sleeve cuff ribbing and preshrunk to minimise shrinkage

title: Abortion Is Healthcare Tee
body_html:
PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

If you would like to use this art on a placard or to print on your own textiles, you can download the high-res file here.

100% of profits donated to the Carolina Abortion Fund (https://www.carolinaabortionfund.org).

North Carolina is one of the few states in the south west of the USA which is not currently banning an abortion ban. The services in this state will be vital for those who need to travel to access their healthcare, and these people will have spent significant amounts in order to travel, leaving them with less funds to access medical help.

Art by Claire Harrison.

title: Alpaca Hoodie
body_html:
PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

Lonely Kids Club has been live and kicking for ten years now, which is crazy to think about. The brand started when I dropped out of my university degree with a determination to start a clothing brand but no experience and no ability to hold down a job. I had a few rough experiences launching the website for over a month before a single sale came in, and also overheard my friends parents throwing shade at me during a dinner but over the years I (almost) figured stuff out and to the surprise of pretty much everyone nearly a decade later we are still going strong.

We reached out to one of the first ever artists we worked with Remy Dautin, on a follow up release to our 2013 drop, Moons of Summer. Remy and I have only ever spoke via email but his use of intricate lines and details/spare dot work create minimalist and impactful interpretations of animals, the stars, and our environment.

Art by Remy Dautin.

PRODUCT DETAILS

Mid weight, 290 GSM 80% cotton 20% polyester anti-pill fleece

Featuring pullover hood, raglan sleeves, kangaroo pocket, lined hood, tonal drawcord
Sleeve cuff ribbing and preshrunk to minimise shrinkage

Featuring a custom digital front print
